type: software
title: "AI-powered Surveillance & Censorship Monitor"
authors:
  - family-names: Lian
    given-names: Jie
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0009-0001-7344-7324"
    affiliation: "Harvard Kennedy School"
url: "https://github.com/LIANJie-Jason/ai-surveillance-monitor"
repository-code: "https://github.com/LIANJie-Jason/ai-surveillance-monitor"
abstract: >-
  A real-time command center that tracks global surveillance and censorship
  using AI-powered news analysis. Ingests RSS feeds from 64 sources,
  classifies articles with LLMs, and renders a live dashboard with a 3D
  rotating globe, country-level drill-downs, embedded news streams, and
  AI-generated article summaries.
keywords:
  - surveillance
  - censorship
  - computational repression
  - news monitoring
  - natural language processing
  - political science
